# =========================================================================
# MediRecord - Production API Credentials Example Configuration
# =========================================================================
# Copy this file to '.env.local' and replace the placeholders with your active keys.
# When these keys are supplied, the app automatically transitions from the local
# zero-config mock database/storage to secure cloud database and object storage.

# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. SUPABASE DATABASE CREDENTIALS (PostgreSQL & Audit Logs)
# -------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Instructions to get keys:
# a. Go to https://supabase.com and sign up for a free developer account.
# b. Click "New Project" and input database name, region, and master password.
# c. Once initialized, navigate to "Project Settings" -> "API" (left sidebar).
# d. Copy the "Project URL" and paste as NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL.
# e. Scroll down to "Project API Keys" and copy the hidden "service_role" key
#    (DO NOT share this key publicly; it bypasses RLS policies securely on the server).
# f. Copy the "anon" key and paste as NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY.

